  "body": "#### System information\r\nCPU : AMD 5950x\r\nDrives : 3.2TB NVME\r\nRAM : 128Go\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\nerigon version 2022.99.99-dev\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nUbuntu 20.04\r\n\r\nCommit hash : \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nHaving a stream of new pending transactions in \"real time\" when they reach the node.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nI receive new transactions at a very slow speed, like 8tx/s. (3-4tx/s if I also run my program logic).\r\nAlso, I have 2/32 threads that run at 100% and others at 0% so I'm bottleneck and no other threads are used. \r\nI don't know if it's because websocket and http are on the same port by default (8545) and then the rpcdaemon can't handle to receive data from websocket while calling the node to fetch more data.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nLaunch erigon and rpcdaemon with ws support, then with your favorite web3 client, subscribe to newPendingTransactions stream and write in the console every changes (every new transaction hash) and estimate the speed.\r\n\r\n#### Comments:\r\n\r\nI have no issues with Geth, I had some with OpenEthereum who was slower for streaming newPendingTransactions, Erigon is the slowest. What can I do to improve the speed ?\r\n",
